# Monaco 2018 Racing Report

Formula 1 Monaco 2018 qualifying data analysis package. This tool allows you to download racer start and finish times, calculate lap times and generate reports.
# Installation

Requires Python version 3.8 or higher. Install the package with the command:

```bash
pip install f1_racing_monaco_package
```
# Usage
Basic Commands : 

Analyzing data from a folder : 

```bash
python -m f1_racing_monaco_package --files ./race_data
```
Sort by descending time : 
```bash
python -m f1_racing_monaco_package --files ./race_data --desc
```
Find a specific rider : 
```bash
python -m f1_racing_monaco_package --files ./race_data --driver "Lewis Hamilton"
```
Example of use in code : 
```py
from f1_racing_monaco_package import main

# Analyzing data with sorting by descending order
main(["--files", "./race_data", "--desc"])

# Racer Search
main(["--files", "./race_data", "--driver", "Sebastian Vettel"])
```
# Output format
An example of a top-15 output :

1. Sebastian Vettel     | FERRARI              | 1:04.415
2. Valtteri Bottas      | MERCEDES             | 1:12.433
...
15. Kevin Magnussen      | HAAS FERRARI         | 1:13.393
---

--- ERRORS IN DATA ---
! Esteban Ocon         | FORCE INDIA MERCEDES      | Incorrect time: finish before start
...
! Lewis Hamilton       | MERCEDES                  | Incorrect time: finish before start

If a rider is specified, only his result is displayed :

Carlos Sainz | RENAULT | 1:12.950

# Data structure

The data folder should contain the following files:

abbreviations.txt - codes of racers and their teams.

start.log - lap start time.

end.log - lap finishing time.

File Format:

abbreviations.txt :

SVF_Sebastian Vettel_FERRARI
DRR_Daniel Ricciardo_RED BULL RACING TAG HEUER
...
 
start.log Ð¸ end.log :
s
SVF2018-05-24_12:02:58.917
DRR2018-05-24_12:03:35.321
...

